00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:53.120
We'll start off with the
Google Tag Manager, which

00:03:53.120 --> 00:03:56.630
lets you use tags in your apps
instead of hard-coding values.

00:03:56.630 --> 00:03:59.260
These tags are then
substituted for values

00:03:59.260 --> 00:04:03.300
that you have stored in the
Tag Manager at run time.

00:04:03.300 --> 00:04:06.160
This can, for example, be used
to manage background colors

00:04:06.160 --> 00:04:09.480
of your app, game settings,
and localization settings.

00:04:09.480 --> 00:04:12.810
Since the values of the tags
are stored in the Tag Manager,

00:04:12.810 --> 00:04:15.510
this eliminates the need
to push your entire app

00:04:15.510 --> 00:04:16.880
from Google Play again.

00:04:16.880 --> 00:04:20.160
You can simply change the value
of the tag in the Google Tag

00:04:20.160 --> 00:04:21.060
Manager.

