last version of Google Play

00:05:14.340 --> 00:05:17.210
services, and it's
often a flying start

00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:19.740
with a number of
API enhancements.

00:05:19.740 --> 00:05:21.230
First off is pinning.

00:05:21.230 --> 00:05:23.000
You can now pin
files that should

00:05:23.000 --> 00:05:24.760
be kept up to date locally.

00:05:24.760 --> 00:05:27.190
This ensures that the app
can work with these files,

00:05:27.190 --> 00:05:29.860
even when the user is offline.

00:05:29.860 --> 00:05:32.120
Then we have app folders
which allows your app

00:05:32.120 --> 00:05:35.590
to create files which are no
longer visible to the user.

00:05:35.590 --> 00:05:39.110
For example, to store temporary
files in a photo editor,

00:05:39.110 --> 00:05:41.860
this is the same function
as the application data

00:05:41.860 --> 00:05:45.700
folder in the Google Drive API
that have existed for a while.

00:05:45.700 --> 00:05:49.090
With this version, we also
have Change Notifications,

00:05:49.090 --> 00:05:51.750
which makes it possible
to register a call back,

00:05:51.750 --> 00:05:55.970
and receive a notification when
a file or folder is changed.

00:05:55.970 --> 00:05:58.000
This means that
you no longer need

00:05:58.000 --> 00:06:02.060
to query drive continuously to
check if the data has changed,

00:06:02.060 --> 00:06:04.160
just put the Change
Notification on it

00:06:04.160 --> 00:06:06.910
and the API will call
you when it happens.

